The paper proposes a solution scheme for overlapping community detection on social networks, which falls under the scope of social network analysis. Therefore, cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The algorithmic approach involves label propagation, which is a common technique in machine learning and data mining, suggesting cs.SI (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithm on different types of networks, indicating cs.SD (Software Engineering) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper emphasizes the hierarchical order of communities in the graph, which relates to cs.LG (Learning).
